WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.110
-Maps on mobile devices
have changed the world

00:00:03.110 --> 00:00:04.660
over the last few years.

00:00:04.660 --> 00:00:07.310
They not only provide a
local map in your pocket,

00:00:07.310 --> 00:00:11.420
but also a map of the entire
world, down to street level.

00:00:11.420 --> 00:00:14.840
And even a 3D fly-around
of many major cities.

00:00:14.840 --> 00:00:16.700
In the Maps for Android
Developers course,

00:00:16.700 --> 00:00:19.080
created by Udacity
and Google, you'll

00:00:19.080 --> 00:00:22.140
start by learning how to add
maps to your Android app,

00:00:22.140 --> 00:00:24.200
and you'll progress to
using the street view

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:28.280
API to build a virtual hike all
the way down the Grand Canyon.

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:31.520
Learn about the camera and how
it's used to project a map.

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:34.270
You'll learn about zooming
to different locations

00:00:34.270 --> 00:00:36.670
and changing the camera
tilt and direction.

00:00:36.670 --> 00:00:38.270
You'll learn about
markers and how

00:00:38.270 --> 00:00:40.100
you can place them on a map.

00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:42.530
Take this course to
learn how to transport

00:00:42.530 --> 00:00:44.840
your users from
wherever they are

00:00:44.840 --> 00:00:46.550
to wherever they want to go.

00:00:46.550 --> 00:00:49.620
For more information
visit udacity.com/google.

